import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# List of numerical features
numerical_features = ['age', 'Medu', 'Fedu', 'traveltime', 'studytime', 'failures',
                       'famrel', 'freetime', 'goout', 'Dalc', 'Walc', 'health', 'absences']

# Calculate the number of rows and columns dynamically
num_features = len(numerical_features)
num_cols = 3
num_rows = (num_features + num_cols - 1) // num_cols

# Create subplots
_, axss = plt.subplots(num_rows, num_cols, figsize=[20, 5 * num_rows])

# Iterate over numerical features and create boxplots
for i, feature in enumerate(numerical_features):
    row = i // num_cols
    col = i % num_cols
    sns.boxplot(x='passed', y=feature, data=df, ax=axss[row, col])

# Remove empty subplots if any
for i in range(num_features, num_rows * num_cols):
    axss.flatten()[i].axis('off')

# selection based on relevance to predict 
from scipy.stats import chi2_contingency

chi2_array, p_array = [], []
for column in categorical_features:

    crosstab = pd.crosstab(df[column], df['passed'])
    chi2, p, dof, expected = chi2_contingency( crosstab.values)
    chi2_array.append(chi2)
    p_array.append(p)

df_chi = pd.DataFrame({
    'feature':categorical_features,
    'Chi-square': chi2,
    'p-value': p_array
})
df_chi.sort_values(by='Chi-square')

from scipy.stats import chi2_contingency
import pandas as pd

chi2_array, p_array = [], []
for column in numerical_features:
    crosstab = pd.crosstab(df[column], df['passed'])
    chi2, p, dof, expected = chi2_contingency(crosstab.values)
    chi2_array.append(chi2)
    p_array.append(p)

df_chi = pd.DataFrame({
    'feature': numerical_features,
    'Chi-square': chi2_array,
    'p-value': p_array
})
df_chi.sort_values(by='p-value')

    'svc__C': [0.1, 1, 10, 100],           # Regularization parameter
